{"editorCode":" \t;Searching for Equilateral Shapes\r\n\t\r\n;Luisa's teacher gave her the procedures \"left_side\" and \"right_side\" which are part of the procedure \"equation\".\r\n;The teacher asked her to run them and try to figure out what is constructed by the procedure \"equation\". Then she asked her to look for a equilateral shape.\r\n;----------------        \r\n;----------------\r\n;For further instructions click on the papyrus button.\r\n;----------------        \r\n;----------------\r\n\r\n;Procedures\r\n;.............\r\n;1. \r\nto left_side :x\r\nfd 2*(3-:x)+4*(:x-1)\r\nend\r\n\r\n;------------\r\nto right_side :x\r\nfd 2*:x+5\r\nend\r\n \r\n;====================\r\n\r\nto green\r\nsetpencolor [0 255 0]\r\nend\r\n\r\nto blue\r\nsetpencolor[0 0 255]\r\nend\r\n\r\nto black\r\nsetpencolor[0 0 0]\r\nend\r\n\r\nclean\r\ngreen left_side 25\r\nblue right_side 25 black\r\n\r\n;===================\r\n;2.\r\n\r\nto equation :x :t\r\nrepeat 2[rt 90-:t left_side :x\r\nrt 90+:t right_side :x]\r\nend\r\n\r\n\r\nclean\r\nequation  85 49\r\n;------------\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n","hiddenCode":[],"sceneCode":"","cameraPos":{"x":0,"y":1.2246467991473532e-14,"z":200},"character":"Bird","notes":"  \t\tSearching for Equilateral Shapes\n\t\t\t*******************************************\nTASK 1\n................................\n1. Run the procedures \"left_side\" and \"right_side\" to see what they construct and then run the following commands:\n\n\tclean\n\tgreen left_side 20\n\tblue right_side 30 black\n\n   •    What does the avatar construct at each procedure?\n\n2. Run the procedure \"equation\". Activate the variation tool and try many different values of the variables :x and :t. What does the avatar construct now? \n\n   •    Is this shape equilateral? \n   •    Is this shape of equal angles?\n   •    What changes on the shape while dragging each slider? What remains stable?\n    •    Based on the properties of this shape, can you say it is a parallelogram? \n\n